HEADWORD: Misorder
<hw>Mis*or"der</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To order ill; to
manage erroneously; to conduct badly.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misorder</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Misorder
<hw>Mis*or"der</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Irregularity; disorder.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Camden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misorderly</ent>⟦br⟧
